article.description: Central Michigan beats Ohio 68-57 with big early lead
article.headline: Central Michigan beats Ohio 68-57 with big early lead
article.linkText: Central Michigan beats Ohio 68-57 with big early lead
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- John Simons opened the game with three 3-pointers and a jump shot as Central Michigan zoomed to a 15-0 lead to dominate Ohio 68-57 and snap the Bobcats' two-game win streak on Tuesday night. Simons scored 18 points with four 3-pointers and grabbed 13 rebounds for Central Michigan (17-5, 7-4 Mid-American), which swept the season series with Ohio (9-13, 4-7) for the first time since 1988-89. Rayshawn Simmons added 14 points for Central Michigan. The Chippewas forced 14 turnovers with 10 steals, Simons had three, and outrebounded the Bobcats 40-29. Stevie Taylor led an Ohio surge late in the game with 15 points while Maurice Ndour and Javarez Willis added nine points apiece. Willis was 0-for-6 from 3-point range, failing to hit from deep for the first time in a month. Central Michigan was up by 19 at halftime and pushed the lead to 25 points in the second half.
